physical_examinations.relevant_findings: Upon admission: General: Alert & oriented, No acute distress. HEENT: No scleral icterus, mucous membranes moist. Cardiovascular: Regular rate and rhythm, No murmurs/gallops/rubs. Pulmonary: Clear to auscultation bilaterally, No wheezes/rhonchi/ral. Abdomen: Soft, nondistended, nontender, no rebound or guarding, normoactive bowel sounds, no palpable masses. Digital Rectal Exam: Normal tone, no gross or occult blood. Extremities: No edema, warm and well perfused.
